1
00:00:07,354 --> 00:00:24,919
La Elaha Ella Allah (There is no god except the one God)

2
00:00:24,919 --> 00:00:44,891
La Elaha Ella Allah

3
00:00:44,891 --> 00:01:05,832
La Elaha Ella Allah

4
00:01:05,832 --> 00:01:10,526
Alhamdu Lillah, We praise God.

5
00:01:10,526 --> 00:01:14,392
Wa Ash-hadu Alla Elaha Ella Allah Wahdahu La Shareeka Lah.

6
00:01:14,392 --> 00:01:18,040
And we bear witness that there is no god except the one God.

7
00:01:19,009 --> 00:01:22,561
I started the machine here and all it said was "La Elaha Ella Allah."

8
00:01:22,561 --> 00:01:24,138
It was not planned this way.

9
00:01:24,138 --> 00:01:27,157
But La Elaha Ella Allah is the greatest statement.

10
00:01:27,157 --> 00:01:32,487
It is the statement that will redeem us and will take us back to God's kingdom.

11
00:01:32,487 --> 00:01:38,896
God will accept us back if we believe the statement, La Elaha Ella Allah.

12
00:01:38,896 --> 00:01:41,215
In words and in deeds.

13
00:01:41,215 --> 00:01:43,849
And yesterday, Mahmood made a discovery,

14
00:01:43,849 --> 00:01:47,356
I hope I'm not stealing his Khutba next week, but

15
00:01:47,356 --> 00:01:55,668
La Elaha Ella Allah, you know in Arabic looks like this: لا إلهَ إلاَّ اللَّه

16
00:01:55,668 --> 00:01:59,003
What Mahmood did, he put the gematrical value of these...

17
00:01:59,003 --> 00:02:09,987
L is 30, Alif is 1, 1, 30, 5, these are the numerical values of these letters next to each other

18
00:02:09,987 --> 00:02:22,755
30 1 1 30 5 1 30 1 1 30 30 5 = (19 X 1,584,897,436,901,595)

19
00:02:22,755 --> 00:02:26,243
This is La Elaha Ella Allah next to each other,

20
00:02:26,243 --> 00:02:27,944
expressed in numbers.

21
00:02:27,944 --> 00:02:29,868
And this is a multiple of 19.

22
00:02:29,868 --> 00:02:33,173
It's quite a discovery.

23
00:02:33,173 --> 00:02:40,801
Cause as you know, God's stamp on everything is the number 19.

24
00:02:40,801 --> 00:02:48,658
On you, the number of bones in your body is 19 x 14 = 266.

25
00:02:48,658 --> 00:02:52,608
Excuse me, number of bones is 209 = 19 x 11

26
00:02:52,608 --> 00:03:00,289
and you were in your mother's womb, if you were a full-term baby, 266 days.

27
00:03:00,289 --> 00:03:03,439
This is what we have in the science books.

28
00:03:03,439 --> 00:03:07,747
The embryology textbook at the school of medicine right here.

29
00:03:07,747 --> 00:03:10,236
266 days for a full-term baby.

30
00:03:10,236 --> 00:03:16,102
and La Elaha Ella Allah, the gematrical value is 19 multiple.

31
00:03:16,102 --> 00:03:29,553
I want to reflect together with you, myself and you on the question "who was your god last week?"

32
00:03:31,762 --> 00:03:33,635
Who was your god last week?

33
00:03:33,635 --> 00:03:37,317
Don't answer me. Don't even shake your head. This is between you and yourself.

34
00:03:37,317 --> 00:03:40,064
We're gonna, together, reflect on it, me and you.

35
00:03:40,064 --> 00:03:42,777
Let's start last Saturday.

36
00:03:42,777 --> 00:03:47,488
Who was your god on Saturday?

37
00:03:47,488 --> 00:03:53,772
Did you think about God the majority of the time on Saturday?

38
00:03:53,772 --> 00:04:00,233
When you got up in the morning, did you say Bism Allah Arrahman Arraheem on Saturday?

39
00:04:02,640 --> 00:04:04,507
Lydia, I said "do not shake your head."

40
00:04:04,507 --> 00:04:06,811
Now, I know you did. Ok.

41
00:04:06,811 --> 00:04:08,839
It's between you and yourself.

42
00:04:10,752 --> 00:04:18,469
Did you do the morning prayer on time on Saturday before Sunrise?

43
00:04:18,469 --> 00:04:21,715
Who was your god on Saturday?

44
00:04:23,232 --> 00:04:29,846
You got up in the morning, you mentioned the name of God, Bism Allah Arrahman Arraheem, the first thing when you got up?

45
00:04:29,846 --> 00:04:34,405
Did you make Wudu (ablution)? And prayed the morning before sunrise?

46
00:04:34,405 --> 00:04:39,558
This is what God wants you to do. If He is your god, you did that.

47
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:50,934
Then, you put on your clothes, you had breakfast. Did you think about the milk? It came from blood.

48
00:04:50,934 --> 00:05:04,452
There is those glands in the cow that go to the blood as the source and takes out the protein, a whole bunch of vitamin, the right percentage of fat.

49
00:05:04,452 --> 00:05:08,408
You know you cannot have vitamin A without fat.

50
00:05:08,408 --> 00:05:15,521
The word fat has a bad meaning these days, but really you cannot have vitamin A without fat.

51
00:05:15,521 --> 00:05:17,516
It is bound in the fat.

52
00:05:17,516 --> 00:05:20,180
So, you have to have a percentage of it.

53
00:05:20,180 --> 00:05:26,431
And those glands of the cow, God created them so they will go and get the right proportion.

54
00:05:28,311 --> 00:05:31,713
This is why they supplement the milk with vitamins A and D

55
00:05:31,713 --> 00:05:37,486
because the fat has to have those two vitamins, connected, bound in the fat.

56
00:05:37,486 --> 00:05:39,363
Did you think about the milk?

57
00:05:39,363 --> 00:05:40,953
How white it is.

58
00:05:40,953 --> 00:05:43,264
The standard white is milk.

59
00:05:43,264 --> 00:05:46,240
We use it as a standard for the color white.

60
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:50,390
And it came out of what? Red blood.

61
00:05:50,390 --> 00:05:53,307
Did you think about this and praise God?

62
00:05:53,307 --> 00:05:55,387
Was God your god?

63
00:05:55,387 --> 00:05:58,516
How about the cereal where you put the milk on?

64
00:05:58,516 --> 00:06:00,359
Where did it come from?

65
00:06:00,359 --> 00:06:05,779
Did you think about God for the grain go in the ground, germinating,

66
00:06:05,779 --> 00:06:15,379
giving you seven hundred grains or whatever of wheat or barley or oats or corn or whatever your cereal was or rice?

67
00:06:15,379 --> 00:06:18,928
Did you praise God for that?

68
00:06:21,302 --> 00:06:26,995
Maybe, you put some strawberries or bananas on top of the cereal or peaches.

69
00:06:26,995 --> 00:06:32,155
Do you think about God's creation of the flavor, the texture, the smell, the taste?

70
00:06:32,155 --> 00:06:35,436
God made those.

71
00:06:35,436 --> 00:06:40,267
You finished your breakfast. Did you say Bism Allah Arrahman Arraheem before you started to eat?

72
00:06:40,267 --> 00:06:46,927
There is a commandment in the Quran that says "do not eat from that upon which God's name was not mentioned."

73
00:06:46,927 --> 00:06:48,891
It's a commandment.

74
00:06:48,891 --> 00:06:53,265
And if God was your god on Saturday, last Saturday,

75
00:06:53,265 --> 00:06:56,653
you said Bism Allah Arrahman Arraheem before you ate.

76
00:06:58,632 --> 00:07:04,754
You see, God is helping you to grow and to develop

77
00:07:04,754 --> 00:07:08,027
You finished eating. You changed your clothes.

78
00:07:10,368 --> 00:07:17,184
Did you think about the textiles that make up your clothes, the cotton or the wool or the plastic?

79
00:07:17,184 --> 00:07:21,446
Whatever it is. God made it all.

80
00:07:21,446 --> 00:07:25,192
As you dress.

81
00:07:25,192 --> 00:07:30,357
I bet you forgot to thank God for the heater.

82
00:07:30,357 --> 00:07:34,389
You got up and it was very cold outside. You take it for granted, you get up

83
00:07:34,389 --> 00:07:40,974
you take your shower, and you do your prayers and you eat. You're not thinking that the environment in your house is perfect.

84
00:07:40,974 --> 00:07:43,767
It's not too cold, not too hot.

85
00:07:43,767 --> 00:07:48,994
You take it for granted, but God, God provided that.

86
00:07:48,994 --> 00:07:52,849
And then you got in your car to go to work,

87
00:07:52,849 --> 00:07:56,996
Did you say Bism Allah Arrahman Arraheem before you started the engine?

88
00:07:56,996 --> 00:07:58,929
Was God your god on Saturday?

89
00:08:02,524 --> 00:08:09,564
When you came to that traffic light, you said "please God keep it green, as you approached."

90
00:08:09,564 --> 00:08:19,626
When you crossed on red and you saw that policeman waiting right there, did you say "please God make him blind"?

91
00:08:24,309 --> 00:08:28,101
I mean you have to think of God the whole time. If God was your god, you'll do that.

92
00:08:31,465 --> 00:08:35,705
And if God was your god, that policeman was blind. He didn't see you cross on red.

93
00:08:35,705 --> 00:08:41,555
You become invisible to the police. It's true.

94
00:08:44,193 --> 00:08:46,637
And during work, did you think about God?

95
00:08:48,319 --> 00:08:49,788
Very important.

96
00:08:49,788 --> 00:08:52,693
Because there is too much at stake.

97
00:08:55,694 --> 00:09:00,257
Your happiness here now and forever depends on that.

98
00:09:00,257 --> 00:09:03,645
Remember Luke 12: 29-31,

99
00:09:03,645 --> 00:09:07,403
says "seek God's kingship over you and everything else follows."

100
00:09:07,403 --> 00:09:11,146
Everything else is fixed for you.

101
00:09:11,146 --> 00:09:17,676
We are now in an era of distinction between Satan's kingdom and God's kingdom.

102
00:09:17,676 --> 00:09:21,359
There's a distinction. God's kingdom is perfect.

103
00:09:21,359 --> 00:09:31,364
If you want to have perfect health, perfect wealth, perfect peace of mind and happiness, you have to be in God's side.

104
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:36,817
God is running everything. It's not even funny.

105
00:09:39,851 --> 00:09:47,214
He left for us just one issue to deal with: whether to be in God's kingdom or in Satan's kingdom. That's it.

106
00:09:47,214 --> 00:09:52,776
The rest is not even funny. The things, the words we say.

107
00:09:52,776 --> 00:09:55,481
And we are speaking from experience.

108
00:09:55,481 --> 00:09:58,500
I just don't know how to express it to you that God is doing everything.

109
00:09:58,500 --> 00:10:01,665
It's a very difficult concept to understand.

110
00:10:01,665 --> 00:10:04,917
But first you have to believe it, then God will show you.

111
00:10:04,917 --> 00:10:15,317
First, you believe. Then, God will show you and prove it to you in a very practical way, in a way that you cannot miss.

112
00:10:24,815 --> 00:10:32,648
Was God your god on Sunday, Monday, Tuesday?

113
00:10:32,648 --> 00:10:35,737
There's a system that you have to follow in the Quran.

114
00:10:35,737 --> 00:10:41,867
Did you tell somebody, I'm gonna do something tomorrow or in two hours, without saying IN SHAA ALLAH (God willing)?

115
00:10:41,867 --> 00:10:43,502
Or did you say IN SHAA ALLAH?

116
00:10:43,502 --> 00:10:45,093
God willing.

117
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:50,124
Were you afraid that people may laugh at you?

118
00:10:50,124 --> 00:10:54,041
Or did you say, God willing?

119
00:10:57,174 --> 00:11:00,086
Did you see something you liked and you said Subhan Allah (Glory be to God)?

120
00:11:00,086 --> 00:11:03,621
A flower, or the sunrise or the clouds.

121
00:11:06,754 --> 00:11:09,263
You say Subhan Allah. God be glorified.

122
00:11:09,263 --> 00:11:16,229
You don't have to say it in Arabic. You can say it in your language. God be glorified.

123
00:11:18,208 --> 00:11:26,723
Anything that you like, your health, you're eating something and you taste how delicious it is and you enjoy it.

124
00:11:26,723 --> 00:11:29,458
You thank God for the taste.

125
00:11:33,349 --> 00:11:35,120
Taste, we take it for granted.

126
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:42,001
But when you taste anything, a piece of candy or a piece of meat, you thank God for it.

127
00:11:42,001 --> 00:11:50,980
Jim Brady, Reagan's press secretary, when he was shot, one of the things he lost was the sense of taste.

128
00:11:53,585 --> 00:11:57,279
He cannot tell fish from apple.

129
00:11:59,456 --> 00:12:02,590
This is a blessing that we have and we take for granted.

130
00:12:02,590 --> 00:12:05,902
When you taste anything, did you say "thank you, God?"

131
00:12:05,902 --> 00:12:08,182
God be praised.

132
00:12:08,182 --> 00:12:11,269
This is what it means, God is your god.

133
00:12:11,269 --> 00:12:17,586
This is why the Quran repeats all those people who do know that God is the Creator of the Heavens and the Earth,

134
00:12:17,586 --> 00:12:20,456
the one who created them, provides for them,

135
00:12:20,456 --> 00:12:22,782
but God is not their god. They're going to Hell.

136
00:12:22,782 --> 00:12:24,444
Why does the Quran repeat that?

137
00:12:28,995 --> 00:12:36,690
You know, it's gonna take us two, or three or four months to really get into this act and really have God as our god.

138
00:12:36,690 --> 00:12:38,972
And I'm counting myself for you.

139
00:12:38,972 --> 00:12:42,201
This is why we have to keep reminding ourselves.

140
00:12:42,201 --> 00:12:45,603
Don't feel bad that you forget

141
00:12:45,603 --> 00:12:48,728
or that God was not your god in the last week.

142
00:12:48,728 --> 00:12:56,328
We're gonna work on it. It's gonna take us a few months

143
00:12:56,328 --> 00:12:58,231
because Satan is after us.

144
00:13:00,169 --> 00:13:08,280
So, if you went through this with me and you. found that God was not your god in the last week, don't feel bad about it.

145
00:13:08,280 --> 00:13:10,032
Just work on it next week.

146
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,707
To do that, let us repent.

147
00:13:13,707 --> 00:13:15,708
Tooboo Ela Allah. (Repent)

148
00:13:27,174 --> 00:13:29,531
Alhamdu Lillah, (Praise be to God)

149
00:13:29,531 --> 00:13:30,931
IN SHAA ALLAH, (God willing)

150
00:13:33,173 --> 00:13:36,690
There are two kinds of people in this world

151
00:13:36,690 --> 00:13:40,042
and no third.

152
00:13:40,042 --> 00:13:42,825
A submitter and an objector.

153
00:13:42,825 --> 00:13:46,994
Every human being you look at is either a submitter or an objector.

154
00:13:46,994 --> 00:13:48,464
There is no in-between.

155
00:13:48,464 --> 00:13:52,622
The submitter accepts everything that God does and is happy with it.

156
00:13:52,622 --> 00:13:56,352
He tells "God, if this is what you want, I accept it cheerfully."

157
00:13:56,352 --> 00:13:59,605
And he or she means it. They are cheerful.

158
00:13:59,605 --> 00:14:00,723
They're very happy.

159
00:14:00,723 --> 00:14:03,440
Remember the sign: Happiness in Submission to God.

160
00:14:03,440 --> 00:14:09,451
Sometimes, I feel like putting it back, Submission instead of devotion.

161
00:14:09,451 --> 00:14:12,748
Submission: accepting everything that God is doing.

162
00:14:12,748 --> 00:14:18,069
The objector objects. He or she doesn't like what God is doing.

163
00:14:18,069 --> 00:14:22,027
So, the rule is really very simple:

164
00:14:22,027 --> 00:14:26,921
There are two kinds of people: a submitter who's always happy.

165
00:14:26,921 --> 00:14:30,656
And an objector who's always miserable.

166
00:14:30,656 --> 00:14:32,588
And there's no in-between.

167
00:14:32,588 --> 00:14:34,639
You can also put it the other way around.

168
00:14:34,639 --> 00:14:37,257
There are two kinds of people:

169
00:14:37,257 --> 00:14:39,902
A continuously happy person who is a submitter

170
00:14:39,902 --> 00:14:43,401
or a continuously miserable person who's an objector.

171
00:14:43,401 --> 00:14:47,029
It's interchangeable. It's the same.

172
00:14:47,029 --> 00:14:52,612
A submitter is always happy because he or she accepts whatever God is doing.

173
00:14:52,612 --> 00:14:57,307
Whatever is happening, he or she understands that God has a good reason for it.

174
00:15:02,682 --> 00:15:05,023
The objector doesn't like what God is doing

175
00:15:05,023 --> 00:15:06,695
and that's too bad for the objector.

176
00:15:06,695 --> 00:15:10,462
So, remember that and remember to be a submitter.

177
00:15:10,462 --> 00:15:15,345
I don't know which comes first, the egg or the chicken,

178
00:15:15,345 --> 00:15:17,166
but a submitter is always happy.

179
00:15:18,652 --> 00:15:20,586
And the happy person is a submitter.

180
00:15:22,169 --> 00:15:24,002
Now, I have a question for you.

181
00:15:24,002 --> 00:15:27,960
And you can answer me. What is the longest Sura in the Quran?

182
00:15:27,960 --> 00:15:31,120
Sura number 2.

183
00:15:31,120 --> 00:15:33,512
And what is the name of it?

184
00:15:33,512 --> 00:15:37,126
Al-Baqarah, the cow,

185
00:15:37,126 --> 00:15:38,992
literally in Arabic, the cow.

186
00:15:38,992 --> 00:15:44,248
Now, Sura number 2, the longest Sura in the Quran, it is full of laws,

187
00:15:44,248 --> 00:15:53,397
the laws of marriage, divorce, Hajj, prayer, fasting, war, prayers.

188
00:15:53,397 --> 00:15:56,756
It is full of rules and laws, but what is the name?

189
00:15:56,756 --> 00:15:59,069
You know who gave the names to the Suras?

190
00:15:59,069 --> 00:16:01,990
God did.

191
00:16:01,990 --> 00:16:04,093
So, why did God pick out the cow?

192
00:16:04,093 --> 00:16:14,394
Of all these subjects in the longest Sura in the Quran, why did God pick out this name, which is rather outlandish, the cow?

193
00:16:14,394 --> 00:16:17,968
You know, the Heifer in English sounds nice... nicer,

194
00:16:17,968 --> 00:16:20,637
But Al-Baqarah, it's in Arabic, the cow.

195
00:16:20,637 --> 00:16:23,535
And in some translations, you've seen the cow.

196
00:16:23,535 --> 00:16:27,038
Why? We have to think about it together.

197
00:16:29,247 --> 00:16:34,936
Because it reflects or it teaches us total and absolute submission to God.

198
00:16:34,936 --> 00:16:40,197
God told the Israelites "sacrifice a cow."

199
00:16:40,197 --> 00:16:46,558
They didn't say "yes, Sir." They argued. "What kind of cow?"

200
00:16:51,076 --> 00:16:56,706
And the answer came back "it's a cow that is not too old, not too young."

201
00:16:56,706 --> 00:17:00,820
And they said "what color?"

202
00:17:00,820 --> 00:17:04,454
They argued back and forth.

203
00:17:04,454 --> 00:17:07,964
So, it became more and more difficult for them.

204
00:17:12,383 --> 00:17:14,623
But do you understand the point

205
00:17:14,623 --> 00:17:17,930
why did God pick out that name for the longest Sura?

206
00:17:21,722 --> 00:17:27,596
You tell the Arabs, there's not a single one here. You tell the Arabs "the Wudu (ablution) is 4 steps."

207
00:17:27,596 --> 00:17:30,767
They say "what's wrong with 9?"

208
00:17:30,767 --> 00:17:35,496
You tell them God says "do not make distinctions among the messengers."

209
00:17:35,496 --> 00:17:39,505
They say "what kind of distinction? Distinction on what?"

210
00:17:39,505 --> 00:17:47,903
This is why God told, the name of the cow, gave the name of the Sura as the cow.

211
00:17:47,903 --> 00:17:50,275
There's a great lesson there.

212
00:17:50,275 --> 00:17:52,902
When God says "the Wudu is 4 steps"

213
00:17:52,902 --> 00:17:56,295
That's it. The Wudu is 4 steps. "Yes, Sir."

214
00:17:56,295 --> 00:17:59,658
And out of all the commandments in the Quran,

215
00:17:59,658 --> 00:18:03,044
after the Commandment "Do not make distinctions among the messengers."

216
00:18:03,044 --> 00:18:06,592
God says "the believers will say we hear and we obey."

217
00:18:09,428 --> 00:18:11,011
They don't argue back.

218
00:18:11,011 --> 00:18:13,197
They don't say "distinction in what?"

219
00:18:13,197 --> 00:18:16,449
They all say that "distinction is what?"

220
00:18:19,780 --> 00:18:21,878
They're insisting on going to hell.

221
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:26,631
So, God is teaching us very early in the Quran,

222
00:18:26,631 --> 00:18:29,486
that whatever He says, we say "yes, Sir."

223
00:18:29,486 --> 00:18:31,239
And we do it.

224
00:18:31,239 --> 00:18:33,342
Without argument.